President Obama has nominated Catherine Friend Easterly for the District of Columbia Court of Appeals. Easterly is currently an attorney in the Special Litigation Division of the Public Defender Service for the District of Columbia. She has experience litigating criminal justice issues in the Superior Court of the District of Columbia and has also filed amicus briefs in the Supreme Court. Easterly previously worked at a law firm in New York and as an appellate public defender. She holds a Bachelor of Arts degree from Yale College and a law degree from the University of Virginia School of Law.